  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Eradicating Child Labour in Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Project&#x2019;s expected effect(s) on society is Reduction of all forms of Child Labour in Greater Kampala Area and Busoga Sub-Region in Uganda (Impact).
The expected effects for the target groups of the Project are fourfold (Outcomes):
Outcome 1: Enhanced understanding and support within communities on child rights with a focus on all forms of child labour
Outcome 2: Improved implementation of ILO conventions (138, 182) and the Uganda National Action Plan for the elimination of Child Labour 2017-2022 in targeted Districts
Outcome 3: Improved social protection for targeted child labourers and families
Outcome 4: Increased capacity of private sector actors to adopt child labour laws and practices at workplaces
The intended target groups are vulnerable children (aged 17 and under) who have experienced child labour or are at particular risks, their families, private sector representatives, local district council leaders.</narrative>
  </description>
